1	//axhob_operation
2	{rbtgo_retriever_divest}
3	
4	NOTE: This operation divests a
5	{rbtr_retriever}
6	{giam_service_account}
7	from the
8	{rbtgi_depot_project}.
9	The
10	{rbtr_governor}
11	reads the retriever's installed RBRA, extracts the SA email from the RBRA's `client_email` field, issues a REST DELETE against the IAM API, and removes the production RBRA file from disk to mirror cloud state and prevent stale-credential reuse.
12	No arguments are required; the target SA is derived entirely from the kindled regime and the retriever's installed credential file.
13	
14	//axhos_step
15	. *Authenticate as {rbtr_governor}*:
16	.. Execute
17	{rbtoe_governor_authenticate}
18	.. {rbbc_store}
19	`«GOVERNOR_TOKEN»` for subsequent API calls
20	
21	//axhos_step
22	. *Read Retriever RBRA and Extract SA Email*:
23	.. {rbbc_require}
24	RBRA file present at
25	{rbrr_retriever_rbra_file}
26	.. {rbbc_fatal}
27	if file missing: "Retriever RBRA file not found — retriever may not be invested"
28	.. {rbbc_store}
29	`«RETRIEVER_EMAIL»` from RBRA's `client_email` field
30	.. {rbbc_fatal}
31	if `«RETRIEVER_EMAIL»` is empty or absent: "client_email field missing from retriever RBRA"
32	
33	//axhos_step
34	. *Divest Retriever Service Account*:
35	.. {rbbc_call}
36	link:https://cloud.google.com/iam/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.serviceAccounts/delete[iam.projects.serviceAccounts.delete] with:
37	... method: `DELETE`
38	... endpoint: `https://iam.googleapis.com/v1/projects/{rbtgi_depot_project}/serviceAccounts/«RETRIEVER_EMAIL»`
39	... header: `Authorization: Bearer «GOVERNOR_TOKEN»`
40	.. {rbbc_require}
41	HTTP 200 response OR HTTP 404 (already divested)
42	.. {rbbc_warn}
43	if HTTP 404: "Retriever service account not found in cloud (already divested)"
44	
45	//axhos_step
46	. *Remove Production RBRA File*:
47	.. Remove the retriever's RBRA file at
48	{rbrr_retriever_rbra_file}
49	from disk
50	.. {rbbc_require}
51	file removal successful or file already absent
52	.. NOTE: Removing the RBRA file mirrors cloud state locally and prevents any process from reusing a credential that no longer corresponds to an active
53	{giam_service_account}.
54	
55	//axhos_step
56	. *Display Result*:
57	.. {rbbc_show}
58	single-line success notice naming `«RETRIEVER_EMAIL»` and confirming divestiture, or a 404-already-gone notice if cloud state was already clean
59	
60	//axhoc_completion
61	Successful execution removes the
62	{rbtr_retriever}
63	{giam_service_account}
64	from
65	{rbtgi_depot_project}
66	and deletes the local RBRA credential file.
67	Cloud state and local credential state are left in agreement: no stale key file remains after a successful divest.
68	A 404 response from the cloud DELETE is accepted as success — the
69	{giam_service_account}
70	is absent either way, and the RBRA file is removed regardless.
71	Proceed to
72	{rbtgo_retriever_invest}
73	to re-issue a fresh
74	{rbtr_retriever}
75	{giam_service_account}
76	when needed.
77

